# Restart Policy

`spec.restartPolicy` ‚Äî what the **kubelet** does when a container exits. Pod-wide, not per-container.

## The three policies

- **`Always`** *(Pod default)* ‚Äî restart on any exit. **Long-running services.**
- **`OnFailure`** ‚Äî restart only on non-zero. **Batch that retries.**
- **`Never`** ‚Äî one shot, win or lose.

## Three subtleties

- **Restart ‚â† reschedule** ‚Äî same node, same Pod, new process. A **node death** needs a controller (Deployment/DaemonSet). *A bare Pod won't survive a lost node.*
- **CrashLoopBackOff** ‚Äî fast crashes ‚Üí kubelet backs off 10s‚Üí20s‚Üí40s‚Ä¶ up to 5 min. Not a phase; the **container** is `Waiting`.
- **Jobs default to `OnFailure`** ‚Äî the Job controller owns whole-pod failure.

## The lesson

> `restartPolicy` heals a **crashed process**. It does nothing for a **lost node** ‚Äî that gap is why Deployments exist.
